{"overview":"A three-voice fugue in A major cast in compound triple meter (9/8), tracing a well-ordered tonal journey through the sharp-side dominant and relative minor before dipping to the flat-side subdominant and a stretto-driven circle-of-fifths descent back home; its most distinctive feature is the systematic exploitation of invertible counterpoint—subject, tonal answer, and flowing countersubject all combine in double counterpoint at the octave—culminating in a stretto passage and a virtuosic sequential episode that sweeps through E major, f# minor, D major, b minor, and e minor before the triumphant A-major reaffirmation.","cross_piece_tags":["fugue","counterpoint","circle_of_fifths","pedal_point","dramatic","lyrical","ternary"]}
